<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>CT — The Internal War</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&family=Crimson+Text:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&family=Rajdhani:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
:root{
  --black:#03070d;--black-mid:#060c14;--navy:#0d1520;--navy-mid:#111e2e;--navy-light:#162336;--navy-border:#1e2f42;
  --gold:#c9a84c;--gold-light:#e2c470;--gold-dim:#6b5520;--gold-glow:rgba(201,168,76,0.10);
  --silver:#8a9bb0;--silver-light:#b8c8d8;--text:#d8e4f0;--text-muted:#7a90a8;--text-dim:#435566;
  --red:#8b1a1a;--red-bright:#c0392b;--white:#f0f4f8;
  --raven:#4a6fa5;--raven-dim:#1e3a5f;--raven-glow:rgba(74,111,165,0.10);
  --enforcer:#8b4a2a;--enforcer-dim:#5a2810;--enforcer-glow:rgba(139,74,42,0.10);
  --culm:#4a0808;--culm-border:#8b1a1a;
}
body{background:var(--black);color:var(--text);font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-weight:400;min-height:100vh;overflow-x:hidden;}
body::before{content:'';position:fixed;inset:0;background-image:url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='noise'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23noise)' opacity='0.04'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");pointer-events:none;z-index:999;opacity:.4;}

.hero{position:relative;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#020508 0%,var(--black-mid) 60%,var(--navy) 100%);padding:80px 32px 64px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);overflow:hidden;}
.hero::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 40% at 50% 0%,rgba(201,168,76,.06) 0%,transparent 70%),repeating-linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,transparent 80px,rgba(201,168,76,.010) 80px,rgba(201,168,76,.010) 81px);pointer-events:none;}
.hero-inner{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;position:relative;}
.ct-badge{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:36px;}
.ct-emblem{width:48px;height:48px;border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);background:var(--gold-glow);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;}
.ct-emblem svg{width:28px;height:28px;}
.faction-name-old{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(11px,1.6vw,15px);color:var(--gold-light);letter-spacing:4px;}
.faction-name-new{display:block;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(12px,1.8vw,16px);color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:3px;margin-top:4px;text-transform:uppercase;}
.hero-eyebrow{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:5px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;}
.hero-eyebrow::before{content:'';width:32px;height:1px;background:var(--gold-dim);}
.hero-kicker{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(11px,1.8vw,14px);letter-spacing:8px;color:var(--gold-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;}
.hero-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(44px,8vw,92px);font-weight:700;line-height:.95;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:16px;}
.hero-title span{color:var(--gold);}
.hero-subtitle{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(13px,2vw,20px);font-weight:400;color:var(--silver);letter-spacing:5px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:32px;}
.vs-divider{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;margin-bottom:40px;}
.vs-side{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;flex:1;}
.vs-company{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:3px;font-weight:700;}
.vs-raven{color:var(--raven);}.vs-enforcer{color:var(--enforcer);}
.vs-line-r{flex:1;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--raven-dim),transparent);}
.vs-line-e{flex:1;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(270deg,var(--enforcer-dim),transparent);}
.vs-badge{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);width:44px;height:44px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;background:var(--gold-glow);flex-shrink:0;}
.hero-meta{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:16px;}
.hero-meta-item{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;}
.official-badge{font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:5px 14px;background:var(--gold-glow);font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;text-transform:uppercase;}

.vote-banner{background:rgba(201,168,76,.05);border-bottom:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:14px 32px;text-align:center;}
.vote-banner-inner{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;}
.vote-banner-inner span{color:var(--text-muted);margin:0 8px;}

.nav-wrap{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;background:rgba(3,7,13,.97);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.nav{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;overflow-x:auto;scrollbar-width:none;padding:0 32px;}
.nav::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none;}
.nav-btn{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:2.5px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-dim);background:none;border:none;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;padding:18px 14px;cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap;transition:color .2s,border-color .2s;}
.nav-btn:hover{color:var(--silver);}
.nav-btn.active{color:var(--gold);border-bottom-color:var(--gold);}
.nav-btn.culm-tab{color:#6b2020;}
.nav-btn.culm-tab:hover{color:#8b2020;}
.nav-btn.culm-tab.active{color:#c0392b;border-bottom-color:#c0392b;}

.main{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 32px 100px;}
.section{display:none;animation:fadeUp .3s ease;}
.section.active{display:block;}
@keyframes fadeUp{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(8px);}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0);}}

.sec-eyebrow{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;margin-bottom:16px;}
.sec-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--gold);letter-spacing:3px;flex-shrink:0;}
.sec-line{flex:1;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--navy-border),transparent);}
.sec-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(26px,4.5vw,48px);font-weight:700;color:var(--white);line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:36px;letter-spacing:1px;}
.sec-title span{color:var(--gold);}
.sec-title .rv{color:var(--raven);}
.sec-title .ef{color:var(--enforcer);}

p{font-family:'Crimson Text',serif;font-size:17px;line-height:1.78;color:#a8bcd0;margin-bottom:22px;}
strong{color:var(--gold-light);font-weight:600;}

.callout{border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);background:var(--black-mid);padding:22px 28px;margin:36px 0;position:relative;}
.callout::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.callout-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;}
.callout p{margin:0;color:var(--silver-light);font-style:italic;}

.mission-block{border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--black-mid),var(--navy-mid));padding:52px 40px;margin:40px 0;text-align:center;position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.mission-block::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 50%,var(--gold-glow),transparent);pointer-events:none;}
.mission-block::after{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold),transparent);}
.mission-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:5px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;}
.mission-text{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(16px,2.8vw,26px);font-weight:600;line-height:1.65;color:var(--white);position:relative;}
.mission-text span{color:var(--gold);}
.mission-text .rv{color:#7aa8d8;}
.mission-text .ef{color:#d4845a;}

/* HISTORY / ARCS */
.arc{padding:36px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.arc:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.arc-header{display:flex;gap:20px;align-items:flex-start;margin-bottom:16px;}
.arc-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:32px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold-dim);line-height:1;min-width:52px;flex-shrink:0;}
.arc-meta{flex:1;}
.arc-era{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;}
.arc-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;}
.arc-body p{font-family:'Crimson Text',serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#9aafc4;margin-bottom:16px;}
.arc-body p:last-child{margin-bottom:0;}
.arc-stat{display:inline-block;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:4px 12px;background:var(--gold-glow);margin-top:12px;margin-right:6px;}

/* RECORD */
.record-hero{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px;margin:36px 0;}
.record-stat{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:32px 24px;text-align:center;position:relative;}
.record-stat::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.record-stat-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(28px,5vw,48px);font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px;}
.record-stat-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;}
.record-section{margin:40px 0;}
.record-section-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.record-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(30,47,66,.5);}
.record-row:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.record-rank{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--gold-dim);min-width:28px;flex-shrink:0;}
.record-name{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text);flex:1;}
.record-val{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:15px;color:var(--gold);font-weight:600;}
.record-sub{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--text-dim);letter-spacing:.5px;}
.era-split{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin:24px 0;}
.era-card{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px;}
.era-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.era-stat{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:8px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(30,47,66,.4);}
.era-stat:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.era-stat-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);}
.era-stat-val{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--gold);}

/* EVENTS */
.event-category{margin:40px 0;}
.event-category-header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;margin-bottom:20px;}
.event-category-icon{width:40px;height:40px;border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);background:var(--gold-glow);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--gold);font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;}
.event-category-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:1px;}
.event-category-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:.5px;margin-top:2px;}
.event-card{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:24px 28px;margin-bottom:2px;transition:border-left-color .2s;}
.event-card:hover{border-left-color:var(--gold);}
.event-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.event-tag{display:inline-block;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:3px 10px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.event-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.event-rule{display:flex;gap:10px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);line-height:1.55;margin-top:6px;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.event-rule::before{content:'—';color:var(--gold-dim);flex-shrink:0;}
.event-payout{display:inline-block;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);margin-top:10px;}

/* ROLES */
.roles-exec{margin:36px 0;}
.exec-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin-bottom:2px;}
.exec-card{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:24px 28px;position:relative;}
.exec-card::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.exec-title-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;}
.exec-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:4px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.exec-abbr{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-dim);letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.exec-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.exec-note{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:1px;color:var(--text-dim);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:3px 8px;display:inline-block;margin-top:8px;}
.two-col{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin:36px 0;}
.col-card{padding:32px 28px;position:relative;}
.col-raven{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#08121e,var(--black-mid));border-top:3px solid var(--raven-dim);transition:border-color .2s;}
.col-raven:hover{border-top-color:var(--raven);}
.col-enforcer{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#120806,var(--black-mid));border-top:3px solid var(--enforcer-dim);transition:border-color .2s;}
.col-enforcer:hover{border-top-color:var(--enforcer);}
.col-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;}
.col-raven .col-label{color:var(--raven);}
.col-enforcer .col-label{color:var(--enforcer);}
.col-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:20px;letter-spacing:1px;}
.col-raven .col-title{color:#7aa8d8;}
.col-enforcer .col-title{color:#d4845a;}
.rank-item{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.rank-item:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.rank-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;min-width:28px;flex-shrink:0;}
.col-raven .rank-num{color:var(--raven);}
.col-enforcer .rank-num{color:var(--enforcer);}
.rank-name{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text);letter-spacing:.5px;}
.rank-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-left:auto;letter-spacing:.3px;text-align:right;flex-shrink:0;}
.pcs-tier{border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);padding:16px 20px;margin-bottom:2px;background:var(--black-mid);transition:border-color .2s;}
.pcs-tier:hover{border-left-color:var(--gold);}
.pcs-tier-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;}
.pcs-tier-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:6px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.pcs-tier-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.entry-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px;margin:24px 0;}
.entry-card{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:20px 24px;}
.entry-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--gold-light);margin-bottom:6px;}
.entry-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;letter-spacing:.3px;}

/* BYLAWS */
.bylaw-section{margin:40px 0;}
.bylaw-section-num{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;}
.bylaw-section-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.bylaw-body{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.75;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.bylaw-item{display:flex;gap:12px;margin-bottom:10px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.bylaw-item::before{content:'—';color:var(--gold-dim);flex-shrink:0;}
.bylaw-sub{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--silver-light);margin:16px 0 8px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.bylaw-divider{height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);margin:36px 0;}
.bylaw-highlight{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:20px 24px;margin:20px 0;}
.bylaw-highlight-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;}
.bylaw-highlight-text{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;}

/* DIPLOMACY */
.diplo-layer{margin:36px 0;}
.diplo-layer-header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;margin-bottom:20px;}
.diplo-layer-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:28px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold-dim);line-height:1;min-width:44px;}
.diplo-layer-meta{flex:1;}
.diplo-layer-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:1px;}
.diplo-layer-scope{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;}
.diplo-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:2px;margin-bottom:2px;}
.diplo-card{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:20px 24px;transition:border-color .2s;}
.diplo-card:hover{border-color:var(--gold-dim);}
.diplo-status{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--gold-light);margin-bottom:6px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.diplo-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;letter-spacing:.3px;}

/* DROPDOWNS */
.dd-wrap{margin-bottom:2px;}
.dd-header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:18px 24px;cursor:pointer;user-select:none;transition:background .2s;}
.dd-header:hover{background:rgba(201,168,76,.03);}
.dd-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;}
.dd-meta{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;flex-shrink:0;}
.dd-arrow{font-size:10px;color:var(--gold-dim);transition:transform .2s;margin-left:8px;}
.dd-arrow.open{transform:rotate(180deg);}
.dd-body{display:none;padding:0 24px 20px;}
.dd-body.open{display:block;}


.command-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin:36px 0;}
.command-card{padding:28px;}
.command-raven{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#07101a,var(--black-mid));}
.command-enforcer{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#100806,var(--black-mid));}
.command-neutral{background:var(--black-mid);grid-column:1/-1;}
.command-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.command-raven .command-label{color:var(--raven);}
.command-enforcer .command-label{color:var(--enforcer);}
.command-neutral .command-label{color:var(--gold);}
.command-item{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.command-item:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.command-rank{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;min-width:180px;flex-shrink:0;}
.command-raven .command-rank{color:#7aa8d8;}
.command-enforcer .command-rank{color:#d4845a;}
.command-neutral .command-rank{color:var(--gold-light);}
.command-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.note-pill{display:inline-block;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;padding:3px 10px;border:1px solid var(--navy-border);color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:8px;}
.system-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:2px;margin:36px 0;}
.system-card{background:var(--black-mid);padding:28px;border-top:2px solid var(--navy-border);transition:border-color .2s;}
.system-card:hover{border-top-color:var(--gold);}
.system-num{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;}
.system-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:1px;}
.system-tag{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--silver);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;padding-bottom:16px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.system-card p{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.rule-item{display:flex;gap:10px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;margin-top:10px;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.rule-item::before{content:'—';color:var(--text-dim);flex-shrink:0;}
.threat-clause{border:1px solid var(--navy-border);background:var(--black-mid);padding:40px;margin:36px 0;position:relative;}
.threat-clause::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.threat-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:1px;}
.threat-sub{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;}
.threat-item{display:flex;gap:12px;margin-bottom:10px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;}
.threat-item::before{content:'—';color:var(--text-dim);flex-shrink:0;}
.defection-tier{display:flex;gap:20px;background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:2px;transition:border-left-color .2s;}
.defection-tier:hover{border-left-color:var(--gold);}
.defection-rank{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);min-width:80px;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1.4;}
.defection-content{flex:1;}
.defection-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;color:var(--white);font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px;letter-spacing:.5px;}
.defection-desc{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.trial-block{background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:32px;margin:24px 0;position:relative;}
.trial-block::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.trial-num{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;}
.trial-name{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:1px;}
.trial-rule{display:flex;gap:12px;margin-bottom:8px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.55;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.trial-rule::before{content:'—';color:var(--text-dim);flex-shrink:0;}
.vote-result{border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);background:var(--black-mid);padding:40px;margin:36px 0;position:relative;}
.vote-result::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold),transparent);}
.vote-result-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:2px;}
.vote-result-sub{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px;}
.vote-bars{margin-bottom:32px;}
.vote-bar-row{margin-bottom:16px;}
.vote-bar-label{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:8px;}
.vote-bar-track{height:8px;background:var(--navy-border);position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.vote-bar-fill{height:100%;transition:width 1s ease;}
.vb-iw{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),var(--gold));}
.vb-p3{background:linear-gradient(90deg,#1e3a5f,var(--raven));}
.vote-stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px;}
.vote-stat{background:var(--black);padding:20px;text-align:center;}
.vote-stat-num{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:28px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:6px;}
.vote-stat-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-dim);}
.vote-note{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-dim);text-align:center;margin-top:20px;line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;}
.culm-lock{display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:480px;text-align:center;padding:60px 32px;}
.culm-lock-icon{width:64px;height:64px;border:1px solid var(--culm-border);background:rgba(139,26,26,.1);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin:0 auto 28px;}
.culm-lock-icon svg{width:28px;height:28px;stroke:#8b1a1a;fill:none;stroke-width:1.5;}
.culm-lock-title{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#8b2a2a;letter-spacing:3px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.culm-lock-sub{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--culm-border);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;}
.culm-lock-body{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);letter-spacing:.5px;line-height:1.7;max-width:340px;margin:0 auto;}
.culm-lock-border{border:1px solid var(--culm-border);padding:48px 40px;position:relative;width:100%;max-width:480px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;}
.culm-lock-border::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--culm-border),transparent);}
.error-code{font-family:'Rajdhani',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:#4a1515;margin-top:20px;}
.closing-box{border:1px solid var(--navy-border);background:var(--black-mid);padding:56px 40px;text-align:center;position:relative;overflow:hidden;margin-top:48px;}
.closing-box::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);}
.closing-big{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(20px,4vw,38px);font-weight:700;line-height:1.4;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:24px;letter-spacing:2px;}
.closing-big span{color:var(--gold);}
.closing-big .rv{color:var(--raven);}
.closing-big .ef{color:var(--enforcer);}
.sec-nav{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-top:56px;padding-top:28px;border-top:1px solid var(--navy-border);}
.sec-nav-btn{font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-dim);background:none;border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:11px 22px;cursor:pointer;transition:color .2s,border-color .2s,background .2s;}
.sec-nav-btn:hover{color:var(--gold);border-color:var(--gold-dim);background:var(--gold-glow);}
.sec-nav-btn.culm{color:#6b2020;border-color:#6b2020;}
.sec-nav-btn.culm:hover{color:#c0392b;border-color:#c0392b;background:rgba(139,32,32,.08);}
.sec-nav-label{font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;}
@media(max-width:640px){
  .two-col,.command-grid,.system-grid,.era-split,.exec-grid,.diplo-grid,.record-hero,.entry-grid,.vote-stats{grid-template-columns:1fr;}
  .command-neutral{grid-column:1;}
  .main{padding:40px 20px 80px;}
  .nav{padding:0 16px;}
  .hero{padding:56px 20px 48px;}
  .mission-block,.closing-box{padding:40px 24px;}
  .vote-result{padding:28px 20px;}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="ct-badge">
      <div class="ct-emblem"><svg viewBox="0 0 28 28" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polygon points="14,2 16.5,9 24,9 18,14 20.5,21 14,16.5 7.5,21 10,14 4,9 11.5,9" fill="#c9a84c" opacity="0.9"/></svg></div>
      <div>
        <span class="faction-name-old">Cross Termination</span>
        <span class="faction-name-new">The Internal War</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">Official Faction Website</div>
    <div class="hero-kicker">Year Three Begins</div>
    <div class="hero-title">THE <span>INTERNAL</span><br>WAR</div>
    <div class="hero-subtitle">Two Companies. One Faction. No Neutral Ground.</div>
    <div class="vs-divider">
      <div class="vs-side"><div class="vs-company vs-raven">Raven Company</div><div class="vs-line-r"></div></div>
      <div class="vs-badge">VS</div>
      <div class="vs-side" style="justify-content:flex-end;"><div class="vs-line-e"></div><div class="vs-company vs-enforcer">Enforcer Company</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">Cross Termination &nbsp;·&nbsp; War Council &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last Updated April 23, 2026</div>
      <div class="official-badge">2nd Anniversary</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- LANDING SCREEN -->
<div id="landing" style="position:fixed;inset:0;z-index:9999;background:var(--black);display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:40px;">
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 50% 40%,rgba(201,168,76,.06) 0%,transparent 70%);pointer-events:none;"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;max-width:600px;">
    <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:6px;color:var(--gold-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;">Cross Termination</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(32px,6vw,64px);font-weight:700;color:var(--white);line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px;">THE INTERNAL</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(32px,6vw,64px);font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:40px;">WAR</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Crimson Text',serif;font-size:clamp(15px,2.2vw,18px);line-height:1.85;color:#7a90a8;margin-bottom:48px;max-width:480px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
      Two years ago a small group decided cross-teaming in NBTF wasn't going to fly anymore. Nobody asked them to. Nobody backed them. They just showed up and handled it — session after session, for two years straight.
      <br><br>
      The mission is complete. Now we fight each other.
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:16px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:48px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">600+ Operations</div>
      <div style="color:var(--navy-border);">·</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">224W / 53L</div>
      <div style="color:var(--navy-border);">·</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">250+ Members</div>
      <div style="color:var(--navy-border);">·</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;">Year Three</div>
    </div>
    <button onclick="enterSite()" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:4px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);background:none;border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:16px 48px;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;position:relative;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(201,168,76,0.08)';this.style.borderColor='var(--gold)';" onmouseout="this.style.background='none';this.style.borderColor='var(--gold-dim)';">
      Enter
    </button>
    <div style="margin-top:24px;font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">April 22, 2026 · 2nd Anniversary</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nav-wrap">
  <nav class="nav">
    <button class="nav-btn active" onclick="show('home',this)">Home</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('mission',this)">Mission</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('history',this)">History</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('record',this)">Record</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('roles',this)">Roles</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('rankspromo',this)">Ranks & Promotions</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('events',this)">Events</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('systems',this)">Systems</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('defection',this)">Defection</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('diplomacy',this)">Diplomacy</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('bylaws',this)">Bylaws</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('vote',this)">The Vote</button>
    <button class="nav-btn culm-tab" onclick="show('culmination',this)">⚑ Culmination</button>
  </nav>
</div>

<div class="main">

  <!-- HOME -->
  <div id="home" class="section active">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">—</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title"><span>Cross Termination</span><br>The Internal War</div>
    <p>CT is a faction built inside Nuclear Blast Testing Facility. For two years we hunted crossteamers, protected cores, and fought every war that came our way. NBTF eventually moved to enforce what we had been doing since day one. The mission was complete.</p>
    <p>We didn't stop. We turned the war inward.</p>

    <div class="mission-block">
      <div class="mission-label">What Is The Internal War</div>
      <div class="mission-text">
        <span class="rv">Raven Company</span> and <span class="ef">Enforcer Company</span> —<br>
        the same two armies that fought the Eternal War side by side<br>
        now face each other.<br><br>
        <span>Organized. Honorable. Ongoing.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin:40px 0;">
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:36px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px;">600+</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Total Operations</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:36px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px;">81%</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">All-Time Win Rate</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:36px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px;">250+</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Peak Members</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;margin:40px 0;">
      <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#08121e,var(--black-mid));border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:3px solid var(--raven-dim);padding:32px 28px;">
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--raven);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;">Intelligence & Reconnaissance</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;color:#7aa8d8;margin-bottom:16px;">Raven Company</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;">Ravens are CT's eyes. Surveillance, reconnaissance, covert operations, precision strikes. If you play smart, patient, and calculated — this is your company.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#120806,var(--black-mid));border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:3px solid var(--enforcer-dim);padding:32px 28px;">
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--enforcer);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;">Elite Combat Operations</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;color:#d4845a;margin-bottom:16px;">Enforcer Company</div>
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;">Enforcers are CT's fist. Direct confrontations, high-risk operations, frontline combat. If you play aggressive, dominant, and head-on — this is your company.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);background:var(--black-mid);padding:40px;margin:40px 0;text-align:center;position:relative;">
      <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--gold),transparent);"></div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:5px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;">Join Cross Termination</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:clamp(18px,3vw,28px);font-weight:700;color:var(--white);margin-bottom:12px;">Pick your side. Earn your rank.<br>Write your chapter.</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:32px;letter-spacing:.3px;">Join the Roblox group first, then access the Discord server to get started.</div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="https://www.roblox.com/share/g/34211543" target="_blank" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:3px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);background:none;border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:14px 32px;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;transition:all .2s;display:inline-block;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(201,168,76,0.08)';this.style.borderColor='#c9a84c';" onmouseout="this.style.background='none';this.style.borderColor='var(--gold-dim)';">Join Roblox Group</a>
        <a href="https://discord.com/channels/704971726215446610/1435822212455207123/1435822212455207123" target="_blank" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:3px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--silver);background:none;border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:14px 32px;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none;transition:all .2s;display:inline-block;" onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(138,155,176,0.06)';this.style.borderColor='var(--silver)';" onmouseout="this.style.background='none';this.style.borderColor='var(--navy-border)';">Join Discord Server</a>
      </div>
      <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--text-dim);letter-spacing:1px;margin-top:20px;">Step 1: Roblox Group &nbsp;·&nbsp; Step 2: Discord Server &nbsp;·&nbsp; Step 3: Pick Your Company</div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-nav"><div></div><span class="sec-nav-label">1 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(1)">Mission &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- HISTORY -->
  <div id="history" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">I</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">CT <span>Historical</span> Log</div>
    <p>Two years. Every era CT has lived through was earned. This is the record of what was built, what was fought, and what was won — before the Internal War began.</p>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">I</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">April 2024</div>
            <div class="arc-title">The Founding</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>Every faction has an origin story. Most of them aren't worth telling. CT's is.</p>
        <p>It didn't start with a grand vision or a carefully drafted plan. It started with a problem that nobody else was willing to solve. Cross-teaming had become a persistent plague within Nuclear Blast Testing Facility — players from one team openly assisting the other, corrupting games, undermining fair play, and making the whole experience worse for everyone around them. People complained. Nothing changed. The problem kept happening because there was no organized force willing to do anything about it.</p>
        <p>A small group of founders decided that was unacceptable.</p>
        <p>CT launched in April 2024 with no backing, no reputation, and no guarantee that anyone beyond the founding group would show up. What it had was a mission worth fighting for and the stubbornness to see it through. The first crossteaming alert dropped on April 28th, sent through a Dyno bot that barely functioned, answered by a handful of members who were figuring it out as they went.</p>
        <p>The early sessions were raw. The system wasn't polished. Not every alert got answered in time. But the faction kept showing up, session after session, alert after alert, operation after operation. In a game where most factions talked about what they were going to do, CT was quietly doing it. People in NBTF started to notice. When CT showed up, things got handled. That reputation wasn't built through announcements or declarations. It was built one alert at a time.</p>
        <p>That was enough to start something real.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">Founded April 2024</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">First Alert April 28, 2024</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">II</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">Summer 2024</div>
            <div class="arc-title">First Blood</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>Nobody outside CT took the faction seriously yet. That was about to change.</p>
        <p>CT was barely 70 members when the call came in. A major faction within NBTF had found itself at war and reached out to CT for support. The relationship between both factions had never been formally defined, no alliance, no signed agreement, just an informal understanding that existed more in practice than on paper. CT raised its banners anyway. When someone calls and you have the means to answer, you answer.</p>
        <p>What followed wasn't what anyone expected. Instead of directing their aggression toward the faction that had called CT in, the opposing force turned almost entirely on CT. The faction CT had shown up to support retreated to diplomatic talks while CT stood alone absorbing the full weight of a conflict it had entered to help someone else fight. It was the kind of abandonment that leaves a mark, not forgotten, not forgiven, just filed away.</p>
        <p>Then it got personal. The opposing faction made a move designed to break CT's spirit. CT's Lead Pacesetter was publicly executed, killed on video and posted directly into CT's server for everyone to see. It was a deliberate humiliation, calculated to demoralize and destabilize. It had the opposite effect. CT didn't break. It hardened.</p>
        <p>When a ceasefire was eventually called CT came to the table. Both sides sat down. The meeting played out calmly and professionally right up until the moment CT pulled out weapons and eliminated both opposing representatives before walking out.</p>
        <p>The faction that had called CT into the war was furious. It was the first real fracture in a relationship that would remain complicated for years. But CT wasn't thinking about relationships in that moment. It was thinking about what had been done to one of its own and making sure everyone understood what that cost.</p>
        <p>The war ended 4-1 in CT's favor. A faction of 70 members had just beaten a force that had picked the fight, outnumbered them, and drawn first blood. Nobody had seen it coming. Nobody underestimated CT the same way again.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">War Record 4–1</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">70 Members</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">III</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">Late 2024</div>
            <div class="arc-title">Building the Machine</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>Winning a war nobody expected you to win does something to a faction. It buys credibility that no recruitment post or announcement ever could. CT came out of its first conflict with something earned and used the momentum to build.</p>
        <p>The member count climbed every week, surpassing established factions. Event attendance grew. The operation that had started with a broken Dyno ping became something structured and efficient. Ravens gathered intel from the Facility side, Enforcers pressed from the Rebel side, and both companies developed distinct identities around their roles. Session after session the machine got better at what it was built to do.</p>
        <p>But CT's leadership wasn't just focused on the mission. While operations ran on the surface something deeper was being constructed underneath. A written constitution. A democratic succession plan. A strike system. A retirement policy. And other classified systems that remain need to know to this day.</p>
        <p>Nobody asked for any of it. Most factions at CT's size were running on instinct and group chats. CT was building institutional infrastructure before it needed it, which is the only time building it actually works. The foundations were laid quietly, without fanfare, by people who understood that a faction without structure is just a Discord server waiting to fall apart.</p>
        <p>CT also competed in an NBTF faction tournament during this period, placing third. For a faction still finding its footing against organizations with significantly longer histories, third place against the full field was a statement made without saying a word.</p>
        <p>Then CT outgrew Dyno entirely. The bot that had sent CT's very first broken alert on April 28th was retired and replaced by something CT built itself. CTBOT launched on February 6, 2025, bringing structured data, real tracking, an economy system, and a level of operational precision the old system never could have provided. Crossteamer names. Teams. Locations. Core safety status. CT stopped flying blind. The mission hadn't changed. The machine running it had become something else entirely.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">CTBOT Launch Feb 6, 2025</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">Tournament 3rd Place</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">IV</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">Late 2024 – Early 2025</div>
            <div class="arc-title">Fire and Blood</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>CT had won its first war. It had built its infrastructure. It had grown. And now the rest of NBTF was paying attention.</p>
        <p>The faction that had started as a reactive crossteaming response unit was becoming something larger, a political force with real weight in the server's faction landscape. CT leaned into it. Alliances were formed. Doors opened. Collaborative events brought factions together under CT's banner for the first time. The mission was still the same but the world CT operated in was getting more complicated by the day.</p>
        <p>CT made one of its boldest moves yet, hosting a large scale inter-faction conference. Established factions and smaller ones alike were invited to a single event, CT's vision of what NBTF's faction community could look like when it worked together. CT ran security. The stakes were real. Midway through the event a hostile group attempted to disrupt it, crashing what CT had spent considerable effort organizing. CT's security held the line. The conference concluded. CT walked away having proven something important, it could build things, not just break them.</p>
        <p>But not everyone in NBTF was interested in cooperation. A group had formed in the shadows with a specific target in mind, CT. Built around individuals who harbored deep grievances against the faction, they made no effort to hide their intentions. They crashed CT operations, disrupted events, and looked for every crack they could find. What made the situation more complicated was that some of its members had direct ties to a faction CT maintained a working relationship with. CT couldn't ignore it and couldn't address it simply. A formal investigation was opened. Evidence was gathered. Trials were held. The connected faction's leadership cooperated and the relationship survived, but it was tested in ways that left a mark.</p>
        <p>The trials concluded. The group was dismantled. Or so it seemed.</p>
        <p>Rather than accepting the outcome several of its members defected into something far more organized and far more dangerous. A new hostile organization had been quietly taking shape in NBTF, one built explicitly around targeting established factions. The anti-CT sentiment that had driven the original group found a new home there and the attacks resumed. Bounties were placed on CT members. Operations were disrupted. The hostility was sustained, calculated, and designed to wear CT down over time. CT tried the diplomatic route first. A formal ignore policy was put in place. It didn't hold. CT declared war.</p>
        <p>The declaration was formal, documented, and unambiguous. CT's terms were non-negotiable, cease all hostile actions, remove all bounties, sign a formal non-aggression pact, and maintain a permanent ignore policy. Until every condition was met CT remained at war. The classified systems that had been built quietly during the earlier arcs were deployed for the first time. Evidence was compiled. The conflict was resolved on CT's terms.</p>
        <p>CT then went further, building a coalition of factions who adopted a formal ignore policy against the hostile organization. What had started as one faction's problem became a multilateral response. The organization was isolated from every direction simultaneously. It never recovered.</p>
        <p>On the external front the same faction CT had gone to war against in its earliest days returned. Not because they had grown stronger — they hadn't. But the grudge was still there and the bone to pick hadn't gone away. CT at full strength met them where they stood. The result was even more decisive than before, a second CT victory. SR conceded. The faction never recovered from it. Leadership collapsed. Activity dried up. The group that had twice made CT its target faded from relevance in NBTF and never came back.</p>
        <p>Through all of it CT's relationship with one of NBTF's most significant factions remained complicated and unresolved. The informal understanding from the first war had never become anything formal. Tensions that had been building since the peace table incident, since the tournament, since months of unaddressed grievance finally reached a breaking point. CT's response was unconventional, a very public propaganda campaign launched directly at that faction, designed to force them to the table when every other approach had failed. It worked. Official diplomatic channels opened for the first time. The relationship didn't become simple. But it became real.</p>
        <p>Fire and Blood. CT had fought wars on multiple fronts, dismantled hostile organizations, survived internal diplomatic fractures, and forced its way into formal relationships it had been locked out of. It came out standing on every front. That had become something of a habit.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">Inter-Faction Conference Hosted</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">Diplomacy Expansion</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">Coalition Built</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">V</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">2025</div>
            <div class="arc-title">Peak Era</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>By 2025 CT had become the largest faction in NBTF history. That wasn't a claim or a goal, it was just the reality.</p>
        <p>250 members. Event attendance hitting double digits consistently. CTBOT logging every alert, every operation, every result in real time. The crossteaming response record held firm, 224 wins and 53 losses across 277 documented alerts, an 81% win rate maintained over the full span of CT's operational history. Ravens on the Facility side, Enforcers on the Rebel side, both companies executing the same mission they had been built for since the beginning.</p>
        <p>CT was firing on all cylinders. The institutional infrastructure built in the earlier arcs was now fully operational, not as a backup plan or a future consideration but as the actual backbone of a faction that had grown beyond what any single person could hold together alone. It ran because the systems worked.</p>
        <p>Then CT's original founder stepped back. Leadership transitioned. The question the faction had never had to answer before suddenly needed an answer. Could CT function without the person who had built it? The Pacesetters kept hosting. The alerts kept getting answered. The operations kept running. The record kept growing. Yes. It could.</p>
        <p>The peak era wasn't without its challenges. Activity had its natural rhythms, strong sessions followed by quieter ones, momentum that built and occasionally needed to be rebuilt. That's the reality of any faction operating over a sustained period. CT weathered it without losing its operational identity. The mission remained. The machine kept running. But nothing at its peak stays there forever.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">250+ Members</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">224W / 53L All-Time</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">81% Win Rate</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">VI</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">Early 2026</div>
            <div class="arc-title">The Eternal War Ends</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>The quieting came gradually and then all at once.</p>
        <p>Late 2025 saw activity slow across NBTF's entire faction landscape, not just CT but the broader community. Sessions that used to fill reliably became harder to predict. The energy that had defined CT's peak era was more difficult to sustain. CT felt it. Events got cancelled. Turnout became inconsistent. The faction tried three new systems during this period looking for something that would reignite what the crossteaming mission had always provided naturally. None of them landed.</p>
        <p>It wasn't for lack of effort. CT kept hosting. Kept answering alerts. Kept showing up even when the numbers weren't there to justify it. Joint faction events still pulled double digit participants. Spikes of activity reminded everyone what CT looked like when it was at full strength. But the consistency of the peak era was gone and the faction knew it.</p>
        <p>The crossteaming alerts had slowed too. The problem hadn't disappeared but it was less frequent, less urgent, less capable of generating the kind of immediate response that had once mobilized CT within minutes. The faction still showed up every time. The win rate held. But the operational heartbeat that had driven everything since April 28, 2024 was quieter than it had ever been.</p>
        <p>Then NBTF announced it would be moving toward official anti-crossteaming enforcement. For most factions that news meant nothing. For CT it landed like a final nail in a coffin that had been slowly closing. The mission that had justified every alert, every late session, every operation run on nothing but commitment and consistency was being absorbed by the game itself. Officially. Institutionally.</p>
        <p>It was a victory. Total, complete, and bittersweet. CT had spent two years pursuing something so relentlessly that the world around it had to change. But winning the war meant the war was over. And a faction built entirely around that war was left standing in the silence with a question it had never needed to answer before. What do we do now?</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">Eternal War Won</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">Mission Complete</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">VII</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">Early 2026</div>
            <div class="arc-title">The Vote</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>CT's leadership didn't panic. They deliberated.</p>
        <p>The question was put to the council formally. Two paths forward emerged from the debate. The first was Phase III, a restructured version of CT's existing model, pivoting toward training, development, and an NBTF tourism center, preserving what the faction had built without requiring a fundamental shift in identity. The second was something that had never been attempted before. The Internal War, splitting Raven and Enforcer into two competing companies and turning CT's conflict entirely inward. The faction that had spent two years fighting an external enemy would now fight itself.</p>
        <p>Phase III was the safer path. It kept CT recognizable. The Internal War was the bolder one, untested, ambitious, and entirely dependent on whether CT's membership would show up for a war against themselves. There was no guarantee they would. There was no blueprint for what it would look like if they did.</p>
        <p>The vote was held. The executive council went 4-1 in favor of the Internal War. The membership cast their ballots independently, 17 of 28 votes, 61% in favor. Both votes reached the same conclusion without coordination.</p>
        <p>CT had democratically voted to declare war on itself. That sentence had never been formed before. Not in any faction, not in any organization operating at any scale. CT didn't collapse under the weight of losing its purpose. It didn't dissolve quietly or drift into irrelevance. It held a democratic vote, made a collective decision, and chose the harder and more interesting path. The Internal War era was approved. The work of building it began immediately.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">4–1 Executive Vote</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">61% Public Vote</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">IW Approved</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arc dd-wrap" style="border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:0;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:20px;">
          <div class="arc-num" style="margin:0;">VIII</div>
          <div>
            <div class="arc-era">April 22, 2026</div>
            <div class="arc-title">The Internal War</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="arc-body">
        <p>Two years to the day from when CT first launched, the Internal War era begins.</p>
        <p>The same two companies that spent two years fighting side by side, Ravens gathering intel, Enforcers pressing the line, both showing up every session to do the work nobody else was doing, now face each other. The rivalry that had always existed between them in the background becomes the point. Organized, honorable, and intentional.</p>
        <p>12 events finalized across three categories. Official War Events where the stakes are highest and the War Council presides. IW Operations where both companies clash in structured competition across NBTF. Company Drills where each side sharpens itself independently. A full event ecosystem built around keeping the conflict alive every session.</p>
        <p>Three new CTBOT systems in development, Mercenary Services, the Public Hitman System, and the Internal Hitman System. The bot that started as a basic alert tool is becoming a full faction management platform with anonymous contracts, defection trial mechanics, and a live economy powering it all.</p>
        <p>CT enters year three not as a faction that survived losing its purpose but as a faction that found a new one. The Eternal War is documented history. The record stands, 224 wins, 53 losses, 277 alerts answered, a mission completed so thoroughly the game itself had to respond. Now the war is within.</p>
        <div class="arc-stat">April 22, 2026</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">12 Events Finalized</div>
        <div class="arc-stat">3 New CTBOT Systems</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">The Legacy</div>
      <p>The crossteaming alert system is preserved as a permanent legacy within Mercenary Services. CT's full operational record remains viewable. The founding mission does not disappear. It becomes the bedrock of everything built after it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(1)">&#8592; Mission</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">3 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(3)">Record &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- RECORD -->
  <div id="record" class="section">
