      <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Primary Hotspot</div><div class="record-val">Core Control</div></div>
      <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Peak Crossteaming Hours</div><div class="record-val">2PM &amp; 9PM</div></div>
      <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Avg Event Attendance</div><div class="record-val">5.6</div><div class="record-sub">per event</div></div>
    </div>


    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(2)">&#8592; History</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">4 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(4)">Roles &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- MISSION -->
  <div id="mission" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">III</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">The <span>Mission</span></div>
    <p>CT was built to eradicate cross-teaming in NBTF. For two years we showed up every session, hunted every crossteamer, and protected every core that needed protecting. The community wanted change. Eventually, NBTF acted. The Eternal War ended not in defeat — but in <strong>total victory.</strong></p>
    <p>The question CT faced after that victory was the hardest one any organization can face. What do you do when the reason you were built no longer needs you?</p>
    <p>CT's answer was the Internal War. Not a retreat. Not a dissolution. A deliberate, democratically voted reinvention.</p>

    <div class="mission-block">
      <div class="mission-label">Cross Termination — Current Mission</div>
      <div class="mission-text">
        The Eternal War is won.<br>
        <span>Now we fight each other.</span><br><br>
        <span class="rv">Raven Company</span> and <span class="ef">Enforcer Company</span> —<br>
        two armies, one faction, no neutral ground.<br><br>
        The war is within.
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>The Internal War is not cosmetic. CT's two companies — Ravens and Enforcers — now operate as genuine rivals. Every event, every hitman contract, every defection trial, every standing update feeds a living conflict with real stakes and real consequences. The war doesn't stop between events. It runs continuously through CTBOT's systems, through the political dynamics of two companies competing for dominance, through the choices individual members make every session.</p>
    <p>CT is not a different faction. It is the same faction that won the Eternal War — now turned inward, by choice, through democratic mandate, with the full weight of two years of history behind it.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">The Eternal War — Preserved</div>
      <p>The crossteaming alert system lives on within Mercenary Services. CT's founding mission does not disappear. It becomes the bedrock of everything built after it. The war on crossteamers was won. The Internal War is what comes next.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(0)">&#8592; Home</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">2 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(2)">History &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROLES -->
  <div id="roles" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">IV</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">Faction <span>Structure</span></div>
    <p>CT operates under a three-tier command structure. The Grand Council governs the faction. The War Cabinet manages operations. The companies wage the Internal War.</p>

    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin:36px 0 16px;">Grand Council</div>
    <div class="exec-grid">
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Chief Executive Officer</div>
        <div class="exec-title">CEO / Chairman</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[CEO]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Highest-ranking executive and overall faction leader. Sets CT's long-term direction, makes major decisions, and ensures all companies and departments align with CT's core goals. Holds tiebreaker and veto authority on War Council votes.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Chief Operating Officer</div>
        <div class="exec-title">COO / Vice Chairman</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[COO]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Second-in-command and the CEO's right hand. Enforces leadership decisions and ensures the execution of CT's strategies and operations. Maintains structure, accountability, and efficiency across all departments. Assumes Interim Chairman if the Chairman steps down.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Chief Human Resources Officer</div>
        <div class="exec-title">CHRO</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[CHRO]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Manages internal affairs, oversees member performance, and administers the staff strike system. Ensures discipline and promotes a positive environment within the faction.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Chief of Staff</div>
        <div class="exec-title">CoS</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[COS]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Contributes to CT's long-term direction through research, reform proposals, and policy advisory. Identifies gaps, recommends solutions, and maintains the faction's institutional memory.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin:36px 0 16px;">War Cabinet</div>
    <div class="exec-grid">
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Minister of Warfare</div>
        <div class="exec-title">MoW</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[MoW]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Oversight of combat doctrine, war strategy, and military operations across both companies. Shapes battlefield doctrine and ensures CT stays unmatched in warfare.</div>
        <div class="exec-note">Suspended — Inactive Until Further Notice</div>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-card">
        <div class="exec-title-label">Minister of Diplomacy</div>
        <div class="exec-title">MoD</div>
        <div class="exec-abbr">[MoD]</div>
        <div class="exec-desc">Manages CT's external relationships, public narrative, and faction-wide representation. Direct point of contact during crises or wartime.</div>
        <div class="exec-note">Suspended — Inactive Until Further Notice</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin:36px 0 16px;">Pacesetter Hierarchy</div>
    <div class="pcs-tier">
      <div class="pcs-tier-label">Tier 1</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-name">Pacesetter Czar</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-desc">Highest Pacesetter tier. War Council voting member and company advocate. Strategic director of their company's Pacesetter program. One per company.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pcs-tier">
      <div class="pcs-tier-label">Tier 2</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-name">Field Pacesetter</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-desc">Senior operational leader within each company. Responsible for hosting events, managing team performance, and supporting the Pacesetter Czar in decision-making. Primary point of contact for members within their company.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pcs-tier">
      <div class="pcs-tier-label">Tier 3</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-name">Deputy Pacesetter</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-desc">Mid-level Pacesetter developing their hosting and leadership capabilities. Supports Field Pacesetters and assists with company operations.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pcs-tier">
      <div class="pcs-tier-label">Tier 4</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-name">Trial Pacesetter</div>
      <div class="pcs-tier-desc">Entry-level staff role. In training under senior Pacesetters. Hosts events under supervision.</div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin:36px 0 16px;">The Companies</div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-card col-raven">
        <div class="col-label">Intelligence &amp; Reconnaissance</div>
        <div class="col-title">Raven Company</div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R5</div><div class="rank-name">Albatross</div><div class="rank-desc">Highest</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R4</div><div class="rank-name">Vulture</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R3</div><div class="rank-name">Eagle</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R2</div><div class="rank-name">Falcon</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R1</div><div class="rank-name">Owl</div><div class="rank-desc">Entry</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-card col-enforcer">
        <div class="col-label">Elite Combat Operations</div>
        <div class="col-title">Enforcer Company</div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R5</div><div class="rank-name">Dreadbane</div><div class="rank-desc">Highest</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R4</div><div class="rank-name">Conqueror</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R3</div><div class="rank-name">Deathbringer</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R2</div><div class="rank-name">Phantom</div></div>
        <div class="rank-item"><div class="rank-num">R1</div><div class="rank-name">Vanquisher</div><div class="rank-desc">Entry</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin:36px 0 16px;">Entry Ranks</div>
    <div class="entry-grid">
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-name">Delegator</div>
        <div class="entry-desc">Training rank. Members shadow both companies before making their allegiance declaration. Must complete the Delegator phase before advancing to a company.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-name">Cadet</div>
        <div class="entry-desc">Entry rank for new members. Undergoes comprehensive training to familiarize with CT's mission, values, and operational protocols.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-card">
        <div class="entry-name">Civilian</div>
        <div class="entry-desc">Non-combative rank for members who support CT without active company participation. Can access Mercenary Services through CTBOT.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">War Council Voting</div>
      <p>Grand Council members and active Pacesetter Czars hold War Council voting rights. Current active voters: CEO, COO, CHRO, CoS, Pacesetter Czar Raven. Threshold: 4/6 majority. MoW, MoD, and Pacesetter Czar Enforcer seats suspended until further notice. Upon reactivation the threshold increases proportionally.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(3)">&#8592; Record</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">5 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(5)">Ranks & Promotions &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- EVENTS -->
  <div id="events" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">V</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">IW <span>Events</span></div>
    <p>12 finalized events across three categories. The Internal War runs on events — from full scale official battles to internal company drills. Every event feeds the war.</p>

    <div class="event-category">
      <div class="event-category-header">
        <div class="event-category-icon">OW</div>
        <div>
          <div class="event-category-name">Official War Events</div>
          <div class="event-category-desc">Scheduled · Announced · War Council Oversees · Maximum Stakes</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:20px;">The biggest events CT runs. Scheduled and announced in advance. Full Raven vs Enforcer battles. Winning company earns full CTC payout — losing company earns half.</p>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Cut the Head</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Official War Event</div>
            <span class="dd-arrow" style="color:var(--gold-dim);font-size:10px;margin-left:8px;">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Both companies deployed into Exterior Security and Interior Security buildings including the holding cells. Objective is to eliminate the opposing company's FPCS before yours get eliminated. FPCS free roam within designated buildings but cannot fight back in regular rounds. First company to 3 FPCS kills wins the round — best of 3 wins the event.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">FPCS track their own deaths — no War Cabinet oversight needed</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Tiebreaker — map expands to Data Center, FPCS can now fight back, no restrictions</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">The Siege</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Official War Event</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Live public NBTF server. Enforcers join rebel side and try to blow the core. Ravens join facility side and protect it. Both companies can coordinate with and recruit regular NBTF players on their respective sides. Codes drop every 15 minutes — Enforcers must collect and execute within the hour.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">1 hour time limit</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Core blows up within the hour — Enforcers win</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Core survives the hour — Ravens win</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">The Death Run</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Official War Event</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Both companies deployed in the Desert Field. Each company has one VIP — FPCS, Pacesetter Czar, or War Cabinet member — seated in a car on their end of the field. Both companies must extract the opposing company's VIP car and bring it to their side. VIPs cannot be killed. Active combat across the entire field simultaneously.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Companies must balance attacking the opposing car and defending their own</div>
          <div class="event-rule">First company to have both VIP cars on their side wins</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="event-category">
      <div class="event-category-header">
        <div class="event-category-icon">IW</div>
        <div>
          <div class="event-category-name">IW Operations</div>
          <div class="event-category-desc">Both Companies · Field Pacesetter+ Can Call · More Frequent</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:20px;">Both companies competing or fighting each other in structured formats. Winning company earns full CTC — losing company earns half unless noted.</p>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">The Purge</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">IW Operation</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Both companies deployed into the same public NBTF server. Objective is to get the most kills on regular NBTF players. Companies can coordinate amongst themselves. Deliberately targeting opposing company members is not allowed — if companies cross paths, kills are fair game. FPCS+ monitors kill log and NBTF live player feed cameras.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">If it devolves into full company warfare FPCS+ can call it and reset</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Highest total kill count on regular NBTF players wins</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Can also be run as an internal company event for rankings</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Safe Passage</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">IW Operation</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">FPCS+ from one company act as VIPs, deciding their own route and objectives within NBTF. That company's members form a security detail. The opposing company hunts the FPCS+ down before they complete their movement. Regular NBTF players are an active threat to both sides. Companies rotate roles each session.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Security detail wins if FPCS+ complete their audit and reach final destination safely</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Intercepting company wins if all FPCS+ are eliminated before completion</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">No Man's Land</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">IW Operation</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Both companies deployed into the Desert Field and Rebel Gas area. Snipers and secondary weapons only — pistols, revolvers, glocks, no automatics. Desert Field provides cover and sniping positions. Rebel Gas provides elevated close quarters combat. Pure combat — no objective, no win condition.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">35 to 50 minutes</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Flat CTC payout for all participants</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Flat CTC — All Participants</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Four Corners</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">IW Operation</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Host selects 4 buildings across NBTF. 4 rounds, one per building. One company defends, the other attacks. First team completely wiped out inside the building loses the round. Eliminated players stay in place until the next building and round is announced. Host decides public or private server.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Companies rotate attacker and defender roles each session</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Company that wins the most rounds out of 4 wins</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Tiebreaker — host calls a fifth building sudden death round</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Iron Wall</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">IW Operation</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Private server required — game commands needed to enhance Juggernaut health. Each company fields one Juggernaut and a supporting squad. Both Juggernauts and squads face off at a host selected location. Juggernauts have enhanced health and auto regen. First Juggernaut down loses the round.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">2 rounds maximum — tiebreaker round if tied, host selects new location</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Company that wins the most rounds wins the event</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Winner: Full CTC &nbsp;·&nbsp; Loser: Half CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="event-category">
      <div class="event-category-header">
        <div class="event-category-icon">CD</div>
        <div>
          <div class="event-category-name">Company Drills</div>
          <div class="event-category-desc">Single Company · Internal · Run Separately · Base CTC TBD</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:20px;">Internal company events. Ravens train with Ravens, Enforcers train with Enforcers. Skill building and company chemistry. Base CTC payout for all participants — amount TBD.</p>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Mark and Execute</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Company Drill</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Run separately per company. 1-2 scouts deployed first to locate and track a high value target — NBTF executive or senior military member. Scout monitors target without alerting them and reports to the strike team. Strike team moves in and ambushes. Ravens emphasize covert infiltration and precision. Enforcers emphasize aggressive ambush and overwhelming force.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Successful hit confirmed by screenshot</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Higher ranking target earns higher CTC payout</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Base CTC — All Participants</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Silent Strike</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Company Drill · Raven Exclusive</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Raven exclusive internal operation. Ravens coordinate a series of ambushes across the server using map keywords only for communication. Attendees gather in vehicles, locate groups of interest, take positions, and strike simultaneously. Return to vehicles after each strike and repeat.</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Map keyword communication only — no open callouts</div>
          <div class="event-rule">Kill count tracked by FPCS+</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Base CTC — All Participants</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">CQC Training</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Company Drill</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Run separately per company. Series of 1v1s, 2v2s, and 2v1s at random locations. Two rounds of mid and close range sniper battle with attendees split into equal teams. Focus on precision, positioning, and movement in tight spaces.</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Base CTC — All Participants</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div class="event-name" style="margin:0;">Patrol Raids</div><div class="event-tag" style="margin:4px 0 0;">Company Drill · Cadet Onboarding</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="event-desc">Cadet onboarding drill. Cadets patrol a designated building while the host hides a rebel inside to test their ability to clear it. CT map codes, radio communication, and formations enforced throughout. Time limit set by host to ensure speed alongside accuracy.</div>
          <div class="event-payout">Base CTC — All Participants</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(5)">&#8592; Ranks & Promotions</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">7 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(7)">Systems &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- SYSTEMS -->
  <div id="systems" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">VI</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">CT <span>Systems</span></div>
    <p>Three CTBOT systems power the Internal War. Each operates independently but feeds into the same living conflict.</p>

    <div style="margin:36px 0;">
      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:2px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">System 01</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);letter-spacing:1px;">Mercenary Services</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--silver);text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">Open to All NBTF Players · Join as Civilian</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;">Any NBTF player can request CT backup through CTBOT. Submit a request through the two-step UI — select a category, then specify the subcategory. Opted-in CT members receive a ping and respond at their own discretion. The crossteaming alert system is preserved and integrated here as Crossteamer Response.</p>
          <div class="rule-item">Combat Support — Raid, Skirmish/Backup, Building Takeover</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Objective Support — Hacking, Code Finding, Core Blowing/Cooling/Defending</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Crossteamer Response — Legacy alert system, preserved and active</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Something Else — Free text field, max 150 characters</div>
          <div class="rule-item">A thread is created under each ping for coordination</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:2px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">System 02</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);letter-spacing:1px;">Public Hitman System</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--silver);text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">Civilian+ · Any CT Member Can Claim</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;">Any CT member at Civilian rank or above can place a hit on any target inside or outside the faction. Submit the target through CTBOT. Any CT member can claim and fulfill the contract. Proof of kill is a screenshot submitted for FPCS+ review and payout. Contracts expire after 48 hours.</p>
          <div class="rule-item">Hit on a non-CT target — any CT member can claim, no duel mechanics</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Hit on a CT member — auto-routes to IHTMS mechanics, opposing company claims only</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Same-company hits blocked — use IHTMS instead</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Contractor identity anonymous — target can only learn it from the hitman directly</div>
          <div class="rule-item">48-hour contract timer — auto-expires if unfulfilled, no refunds</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:2px solid var(--gold-dim);">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">System 03</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gold);letter-spacing:1px;">IHTMS — Internal Hitman System</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--silver);text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px;">Delegator+ · Internal War Exclusive</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.65;letter-spacing:.3px;">The Internal War's most politically charged mechanic. Delegator-ranked members and above can place anonymous contracts on opposing company members through CTBOT. The opposing company claims and fulfills the hit. What makes IHTMS unique is that the target can fight back. Upon receiving an active hit, targets can invoke a Duel Exemption, challenging the contractor to a 1v1 the contractor must accept, produce a champion for, or withdraw the hit. Targets can also escalate to a Squad Duel, bringing up to 3 company members into a full 4v4. Either outcome resolves the contract completely.</p>
          <div class="rule-item">Hit on a Raven — only Enforcers can claim. Hit on an Enforcer — only Ravens can claim</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Same-company hits permitted — if contractor is identified, a Defection Trial follows</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Contractor identity fully anonymous — CTBOT never reveals it</div>
          <div class="rule-item">48-hour contract timer — auto-expires if unfulfilled</div>
          <div class="rule-item">Proof of kill is a screenshot submitted for FPCS+ manual review and payout</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">Duel Exemption — IHTMS Only</div>
      <p>When a hit is active through IHTMS, the target has two options. Invoke a <strong>Duel Exemption</strong> — challenging the contractor to a 1v1. The contractor must accept, produce a champion, or withdraw the hit. Or escalate to a <strong>Squad Duel</strong> — up to 3 company members in a full 4v4 skirmish. Either way, the duel resolves the contract entirely — win or lose, the hitman is paid out and the contract closes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(6)">&#8592; Events</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">8 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(8)">Defection &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- DEFECTION -->
  <div id="defection" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">VII</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">The <span>Defection</span> System</div>
    <p>In the Internal War, loyalty is the most sacred currency. Switching companies is not a casual decision — every rank tier faces a different cost, and every defection is <strong>one time only.</strong> Once you switch, you cannot switch again.</p>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Cadet · R1 · Owl / Vanquisher</div><div class="defection-title" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Sent Back to Cadet</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body"><div class="defection-desc">Returned to Cadet status. Both companies get a formal opportunity to recruit and make their case. Once R2 requirements are met the member makes their final allegiance declaration.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">R2 · Falcon / Phantom</div><div class="defection-title" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Trial I — The Hunt</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body"><div class="defection-desc">No clean switches at R2. You have established yourself enough that your company will fight to keep you. Must survive Trial I to earn the right to switch.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">R3 · Eagle / Deathbringer</div><div class="defection-title" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Trial I — The Gauntlet</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body"><div class="defection-desc">The Hunt pushed to its limit. Longer window, harder conditions, the full company deployed against you. At R3 you have earned your rank through real service — your company will not let you go quietly.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">R4–R5 · Vulture+ / Conqueror+</div><div class="defection-title" style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Trial II — The Sponsored Crossing</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body"><div class="defection-desc">At this rank your defection is a political event. Three sponsorships from R3+ members of the opposing company required before the event is even scheduled. No sponsors, no attempt.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:32px;">
      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Trial I</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:1px;">The Hunt</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:.3px;">The defector declares intent to the War Council. A date is set publicly — the entire company knows it's coming. On the day, the defector spawns anywhere in NBTF. Their company deploys in full to hunt them down.</p>
          <div class="trial-rule">Defector gets a 2-minute head start before the hunt begins</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Must survive without dying once — R2: 20 minutes</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Cannot leave NBTF boundaries during the hunt</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Company members cannot pre-camp the defector's spawn location</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">War Council observes and verifies — result is final</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Survive: switch approved at R1 of new company. Die once: denied until next cycle</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Trial I — Extended</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:1px;">The Gauntlet</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:.3px;">The Hunt at its most brutal. Same format — but the window extends to 30 minutes and the company is given a 90-second warning before the defector spawns.</p>
          <div class="trial-rule">Company receives a 90-second positioning warning before defector spawns</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Must survive 30 minutes without dying once</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">All other Hunt rules apply</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Survive: switch approved at R2 of new company. Die once: denied until next cycle</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);position:relative;">
        <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--gold-dim),transparent);"></div>
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:4px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Trial II</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:1px;">The Sponsored Crossing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:.3px;">Must first secure 3 sponsorships from R3+ members of the opposing company. Sponsors are publicly vouching — their reputation is on the line. No sponsors, no attempt.</p>
          <div class="trial-rule">War Council designates a safe zone — location changes every event</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">3 sponsors stationed at safe zone perimeter — cannot assist until defector enters range</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Defector's current company deploys in full to hunt them across the map</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Once defector enters safe zone range — sponsors can engage and assist</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Defector receives one decoy — a single false location ping managed through CTBOT</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Hunting company cannot enter the safe zone itself</div>
          <div class="trial-rule">Reach safe zone alive: switch approved at R2 of new company. Eliminated: denied until next cycle</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">Public Spectacle</div>
      <p>Every defection event is public — the whole server can watch. The defector who makes it becomes legend. The one who gets caught becomes a cautionary tale. These are CT's most dramatic recurring events and some of its most powerful recruitment moments.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(7)">&#8592; Systems</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">9 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(9)">Diplomacy &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- DIPLOMACY -->
  <div id="diplomacy" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">VIII</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">Diplomatic <span>Framework</span></div>
    <p>CT maintains a three layer diplomatic system governing all external faction relationships. Each layer operates at a different level of the organization and serves a different function.</p>

    <div class="diplo-layer">
      <div class="diplo-layer-header">
        <div class="diplo-layer-num">1</div>
        <div class="diplo-layer-meta">
          <div class="diplo-layer-name">Affiliation</div>
          <div class="diplo-layer-scope">War Council · Faction-Wide · How CT Views a Faction</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="diplo-grid">
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Ally</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Partnered and allied. CT will seek to aid each other during operations and defensive conflicts.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Neutral</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">No significant interaction or balanced stance. Neither cooperation nor opposition.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Rival</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Direct competition with CT stemming from clashing goals or influence within NBTF.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Adversary</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">CT actively opposes this faction. Formal declaration required. No conciliatory efforts on either side.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diplo-layer">
      <div class="diplo-layer-header">
        <div class="diplo-layer-num">2</div>
        <div class="diplo-layer-meta">
          <div class="diplo-layer-name">Entente</div>
          <div class="diplo-layer-scope">War Council · Faction-Wide · How CT Interacts With a Faction</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="diplo-grid">
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Defensive</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Mutual defense agreement. CT and the faction protect each other during external threats but do not collaborate offensively.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Collaborators</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Joint operations or training without a formal partnership commitment.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Non-Partisan</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Neutral coexistence. Neither faction engages in joint operations or shared goals regardless of Affiliation status.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Suspect</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">CT views this faction with caution due to questionable actions or alliances. Monitored closely.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card" style="grid-column:1/-1;">
          <div class="diplo-status">Hostile</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Open hostilities. Faction is considered a threat and treated with direct opposition during public events.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diplo-layer">
      <div class="diplo-layer-header">
        <div class="diplo-layer-num">3</div>
        <div class="diplo-layer-meta">
          <div class="diplo-layer-name">Company Relation</div>
          <div class="diplo-layer-scope">Company Level · Organic · Which Company Holds the Active Relationship</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="diplo-grid">
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Assigned</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Formally working with this company this season.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Active</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Regularly coordinating on operations and training.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Dormant</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Alliance exists at faction level but no active company engagement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diplo-card">
          <div class="diplo-status">Shared</div>
          <div class="diplo-desc">Both companies maintain working relationships with this faction.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">Alliance Rules</div>
      <p>CT maintains a maximum of 3-4 allied factions at any given time. Alliance proposals require a 4/6 War Council vote. Final approval rests with the Chairman who holds veto authority regardless of vote outcome. Alliance termination follows the same voting threshold.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:48px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Diplomatic & Conflict History</div>

      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">SR War I</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">4–1 CT VICTORY</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);">Summer 2024</div>
          
            <span class="dd-arrow" style="color:var(--gold-dim);font-size:10px;margin-left:8px;">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">CT's first war. Fought at 70 members after raising banners for an ally who subsequently retreated to diplomatic talks, leaving CT to fight alone. The Sharlach Resistance targeted CT harder than the faction that called CT in. After CT's Lead Pacesetter was publicly executed in CT's own server, CT agreed to a ceasefire — then eliminated both opposing representatives at the peace table before walking out. The war ended 4-1 in CT's favor. Nobody had expected it.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">External Conflict</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">SR War II</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">2–0 CT VICTORY</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);">Early 2025</div>
          
            <span class="dd-arrow" style="color:var(--gold-dim);font-size:10px;margin-left:8px;">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">The Sharlach Resistance came back. Not because they had grown stronger — they hadn't. But the grudge was still there and the bone to pick hadn't gone away. CT met them at full strength. The result was immediate and decisive. SR conceded after two rounds, unable to sustain the conflict. They never recovered. Leadership problems followed and the faction gradually faded from relevance in NBTF.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">External Conflict</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">GCORPS Conflict</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">RESOLVED — CT TERMS</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);">Early 2025</div>
          
            <span class="dd-arrow" style="color:var(--gold-dim);font-size:10px;margin-left:8px;">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">An organization built explicitly around targeting established NBTF factions, fueled in part by members of a rogue group CT had already dismantled through formal trials. GCORPS placed bounties on CT members, attacked operations, and ran a sustained campaign of hostility. CT declared war when diplomatic channels failed. Evidence was compiled and presented. The conflict was resolved entirely on CT's terms. A coalition of factions adopted a formal ignore policy — multilateral isolation. GCORPS never recovered.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">External Conflict</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">ARC Incident</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-left:auto;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">RESOLVED</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);">Early 2025</div>
            <span class="dd-arrow">▼</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">A rogue group with direct ties to an allied faction began targeting CT operations. CT opened a formal investigation and classified the allied faction as Suspect pending resolution. Their leadership cooperated fully, submitting a formal account of events and choosing to dissolve the rogue group rather than face a full trial. CT accepted the terms. The Suspect classification was lifted. The relationship survived.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Diplomatic Incident</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">ASOC</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-left:auto;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">ALLY · COLLABORATIVE · DEFENSIVE</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold-light);">Active</div>
            <span class="dd-arrow">▼</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">ASOC is one of CT's most significant active alliances. Army Special Operations Command operates at a level of organization and military discipline that CT respects. The relationship has been tested before and came out intact. That means something. CT and ASOC hold a collaborative entente with a defensive agreement in place. When CT shows up, ASOC is one of the few factions in NBTF that shows up too.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Alliance · Collaborative · Defensive Agreement</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      

      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">ORCA (formerly Ferrymen)</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-left:auto;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">ALLY · COLLABORATIVE · DEFENSIVE</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold-light);">Active</div>
            <span class="dd-arrow">▼</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">ORCA, formerly known as the Ferrymen, is a CT ally with a collaborative entente and a defensive agreement in place. The relationship started on the competitive field — CT ran three joint events against them under the Ferrymen name and won all three. They never took one. Respect was earned both ways. They rebranded to ORCA and the alliance carried over. It holds.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Alliance · Collaborative · Defensive Agreement · 3–0 CT</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      
      
      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">TCC</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-left:auto;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold);border:1px solid var(--gold-dim);padding:3px 10px;background:var(--gold-glow);">ALLY · COLLABORATIVE · DEFENSIVE</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--gold-light);">Active</div>
            <span class="dd-arrow">▼</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">TCC is one of CT's closest operational allies, built on shared action rather than agreements on paper. CT and TCC deployed together inside NBTF on joint raid operations, moving as a unified force. The kind of alliance that proves itself in the field. Collaborative entente and defensive agreement in place.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Alliance · Collaborative · Defensive Agreement · Joint Operations</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-left:3px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);letter-spacing:.5px;">HF Dynamic</div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;">
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--silver);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:3px 10px;">NEUTRAL</div>
            <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);">2024 – Present</div>
          
            <span class="dd-arrow" style="color:var(--gold-dim);font-size:10px;margin-left:8px;">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.7;letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:10px;">One of NBTF's most layered faction relationships. CT and Horizon Foundation share a history marked by tension, cooperation, and unresolved grievance going back to the first SR war. At one point CT formally classified HF as Rivals. HF never acknowledged it publicly, committed to maintaining their neutral stance, but everyone knew what it was. CT eventually relabeled them Neutral with a Non-Partisan entente. Formal diplomatic channels opened after CT launched a very public campaign directed at HF that brought them to the table. It has never been a simple relationship. But it has been a real one. CT and HF maintain an active working relationship to this day with an executive bridge between both factions at the highest level.</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;">Diplomatic Relationship</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(8)">&#8592; Defection</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">10 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(10)">Bylaws &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- BYLAWS -->
  <div id="bylaws" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">IX</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">Faction <span>Bylaws</span></div>
    <p>Updated and ratified for the Internal War era. These bylaws govern every aspect of CT's operation — from daily conduct to succession of power.</p>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section I</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Purpose and Mission</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-body">Cross Termination is a unified faction of two specialized companies where both Rebels and Facility members fight under a common cause of internal conflict.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">The Eternal War</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">CT's mission was the eradication of cross-teaming within NBTF. The mission was prosecuted so effectively and so persistently that NBTF itself adopted anti-cross-teaming enforcement as official policy. The Eternal War is won.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">The Internal War</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">With no external enemy left to fight, Raven and Enforcer face each other in organized, honorable, and intentional competition for dominance. The war is within.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section II</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Faction Structure</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Grand Council</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">The Grand Council is the highest governing body of CT, responsible for CT's long-term direction, institutional stability, and all major faction decisions. Grand Council members hold neutrality in the Internal War — they do not fight for either company. They are the sole arbiters of the war and ensure its continuation.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">War Cabinet</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">The War Cabinet sits below the Grand Council and oversees CT's core internal functions and the faction's operational infrastructure.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Chief Executive Officer [CEO]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Highest-ranking executive and overall faction leader. Sets CT's long-term direction, makes major decisions, and ensures all companies and departments align with CT's core goals.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Chief Operating Officer [COO]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Second-in-command and the CEO's right hand. Enforces leadership decisions and ensures the execution of CT's strategies and operations. Maintains structure, accountability, and efficiency across all departments.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Chief Human Resources Officer [CHRO]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Manages internal affairs, oversees member performance, and administers the staff strike system. Ensures discipline and promotes a positive environment within the faction and the internal staff team.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Chief of Staff [CoS]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Contributes to CT's long-term direction through research, reform proposals, and policy advisory. Identifies gaps, recommends solutions, and maintains the faction's institutional memory.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Minister of Warfare [MoW]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Oversight of combat doctrine, war strategy, and military operations across both companies. Shapes battlefield doctrine and ensures CT stays unmatched in warfare.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Minister of Diplomacy [MoD]</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Manages CT's external relationships, public narrative, and faction-wide representation beyond the Internal War. Appointed as the direct point of contact during crises or wartime.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Pacesetter Czar</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Highest Pacesetter tier. War Council voting member and company advocate. Strategic director of their company's Pacesetter program.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Pacesetter</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Leaders within each company, responsible for hosting training sessions, managing team performance, and supporting the Pacesetter Czar in decision-making. Serve as the primary point of contact for members within their respective companies.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Raven Company</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Specializes in intelligence gathering, reconnaissance, and covert operations to monitor both internal and external threats. Ravens act as the faction's eyes and ears, keeping CT informed and ready to act on emerging issues.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Enforcer Company</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Serves as CT's primary combat unit, engaging in direct confrontations and executing high-risk operations. Enforcers provide the strength needed to deal with threats swiftly and effectively.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Cadet</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Entry rank. Cadets undergo comprehensive training to familiarize themselves with CT's mission, shadowing both Ravens and Enforcers before making their company allegiance declaration.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Civilian</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Non-combative rank for members who support CT without active company participation.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section III</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Rules and Conduct</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Conduct</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">All members of Cross Termination are expected to uphold the faction's core values of loyalty, integrity, and professionalism. These standards maintain order, preserve CT's institutional identity, and protect the faction from influences that may compromise its purpose or direction.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Respect and Unity</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">The Internal War is structured and honorable. Actions that promote genuine division, toxicity, or hostility beyond the scope of the war will be addressed promptly. Ravens and Enforcers are rivals by design, not by animosity.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Participation and Activity</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Active participation in faction events, training, and operations is required from all staff members. Members may request a Leave of Absence if unable to meet activity requirements, with a maximum of 15 days per month and 180 days annually.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section IV</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Decision-Making and Voting</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-highlight">
          <div class="bylaw-highlight-label">War Council Threshold</div>
          <div class="bylaw-highlight-text">A minimum of 4 out of 6 active votes is required for a decision to pass. The Chairman serves as tiebreaker when majority cannot be reached. Upon reactivation of suspended council seats the threshold increases proportionally.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Active Voting Members</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Chief Executive Officer (CEO)</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Chief Operating Officer (COO)</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Chief Human Resources Officer (CHRO)</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Chief of Staff (CoS)</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Pacesetter Czar — Raven Company</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Suspended Voting Members</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">The Minister of Warfare, Minister of Diplomacy, and Pacesetter Czar Enforcer Company hold voting rights but are currently suspended until further notice.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section V</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Membership and Promotions</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Cadet Program</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">New members begin as Cadets and undergo comprehensive training to familiarize themselves with CT's mission, values, and operational protocols. Before advancing to a company, every member must complete the Delegator phase.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Company Selection</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Upon completing Delegator training, members go through a three stage recruitment trial — one operation with each company, followed by a deciding battle. At the end they make their final allegiance declaration. That choice is permanent with one lifetime defection available.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Promotions</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Promotions are based on merit, activity, and contribution to the faction's goals. The War Council in consultation with the Pacesetter Team evaluates member performance and determines promotions based on posted requirements.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section VI</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Conflict Resolution and Discipline</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Strike System</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">CT employs a three strike system to handle disciplinary issues. Infractions are recorded by the CHRO. Accumulating three strikes results in removal or demotion.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Appeals and Dispute Resolution</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Members may appeal disciplinary actions by submitting a formal request to the CHRO. The War Council will review appeals and make a final decision.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Defection Trials</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">If a company member is found to have placed a same-company hit through IHTMS and their identity is confirmed, the War Cabinet will preside over a Defection Trial. If found guilty the contractor is forced through the Defection System at their current rank tier.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section VII</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Company Operations and Coordination</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Internal War Operations</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">Raven and Enforcer Companies operate as competing entities during the Internal War. Each company pursues its own objectives, events, and operations independently. The Pacesetter Czars coordinate their respective company's activities and represent their company's interests at the War Council level.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">External Threat Clause</div>
        <div class="bylaw-body">When the War Council unanimously determines that an external force poses a significant threat to CT, its members, or NBTF stability — the Internal War is immediately suspended. Both companies fall under unified command. A unanimous War Council vote is required to both declare and lift the suspension. War standings are frozen during suspension and resume exactly where they left off.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section IX</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Leave of Absence</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-body">Staff members may request a LOA if personal circumstances prevent them from meeting activity requirements. The policy allows for up to 15 days per month and 180 days per year. Extended inactivity without proper notice may lead to reassignment or removal from any leadership role.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section XI</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Bylaw Adjustments and Amendments</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-body">These bylaws are reviewed regularly by the War Council. A minimum of 4/6 War Council votes is required to pass any bylaw amendment. The Chairman holds final veto authority.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section XII</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Retirement Policy</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Staff Retiree Eligibility</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Executive — 5 months held, 3 assigned tasks completed, 300 CTC minimum</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Pacesetter Czar — 4 months held, 15 operations or training sessions, 255 CTC minimum</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Field Pacesetter / Deputy Pacesetter — 3 months held, 10 operations or training sessions, 200 CTC minimum</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Trial Pacesetter — Not eligible for Staff Retiree. Company Retiree available after 1 month with 100 CTC minimum. Member may decline and remain active.</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Company Retiree Eligibility</div>
      <div class="bylaw-item">R4-R5 (Vulture+ / Conqueror+) — 3.5 months, 12 operations, 220 CTC minimum</div>
      <div class="bylaw-item">R1-R3 (Owl-Eagle / Vanquisher-Deathbringer) — 3 months, 10 operations, 200 CTC minimum. Must be Owl+ or Vanquisher+ to qualify.</div>
      <div class="bylaw-sub">Key Notes</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Time can be carried over from previous ranks and positions</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Consultant role given to Pacesetter Czar+ upon retiring after holding position for at least 4 months</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
      <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
        <div><div class="bylaw-section-num" style="margin:0 0 4px;">Section XIII</div><div class="bylaw-section-title" style="margin:0;">Chairman Succession Plan</div></div>
        <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dd-body">
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Phase 1 — Council Nomination Process</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Chairman must provide one week notice before stepping down</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Vice Chairman (COO) automatically assumes Interim Chairman and oversees the election</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">All nominees must hold a current position on the War Council</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Vice Chairman automatically receives a slot on the voting ballot</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Each War Council member submits one nomination — cannot nominate themselves</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">The three most nominated Council members plus the Vice Chairman advance to the primary vote</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">If a tie occurs a tiebreaker vote among the Council determines the final candidates</div>
        <div class="bylaw-sub">Phase 2 — Council Primary Vote</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Candidate with the least votes is eliminated from the primary</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Council votes between remaining candidates to elect the next Chairman</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum of 4/6 votes required for official appointment</div>
        <div class="bylaw-item">If no candidate secures the required majority a runoff election is held between the top two candidates</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(9)">&#8592; Diplomacy</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">11 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(11)">The Vote &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- THE VOTE -->
  <div id="vote" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">X</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">The <span>Vote</span></div>
    <p>CT faced a choice after winning the Eternal War. Phase III — a restructured model built around training and development. Or the Internal War — a complete reimagining that turned the faction's conflict entirely inward. Both sides made their case. The council and the membership voted independently. Both reached the same conclusion.</p>

    <div class="vote-result">
      <div class="vote-result-title">The Mandate</div>
      <div class="vote-result-sub">Poll Closed March 30, 2026 · 23:30 EST</div>
      <div class="vote-bars">
        <div class="vote-bar-row">
          <div class="vote-bar-label">
            <span style="color:var(--gold);">Internal War</span>
            <span style="color:var(--text-muted);">61% · 17 votes</span>
          </div>
          <div class="vote-bar-track"><div class="vote-bar-fill vb-iw" style="width:61%;"></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="vote-bar-row" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <div class="vote-bar-label">
            <span style="color:var(--raven);">Phase III</span>
            <span style="color:var(--text-muted);">39% · 11 votes</span>
          </div>
          <div class="vote-bar-track"><div class="vote-bar-fill vb-p3" style="width:39%;"></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="vote-stats">
        <div class="vote-stat"><div class="vote-stat-num">28</div><div class="vote-stat-label">Total Public Votes</div></div>
        <div class="vote-stat"><div class="vote-stat-num" style="color:var(--gold);">4–1</div><div class="vote-stat-label">Executive Vote</div></div>
        <div class="vote-stat"><div class="vote-stat-num" style="color:#4a9e6a;">PASSED</div><div class="vote-stat-label">Poll Status</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="vote-note">
        Executive vote finalized 4–1. Public vote 61% — 17 of 28.<br>
        Both votes reached the same conclusion independently.<br>
        The mandate is clear. The era begins.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">What This Means</div>
      <p>CT entered this decision democratically and exits it unified. The Internal War was not imposed — it was chosen. By the council and by the membership, independently, at the same time. That's the mandate that launched everything built after it.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="closing-box">
      <div class="closing-big">The Eternal War is over.<br><span class="rv">Ravens</span> and <span class="ef">Enforcers</span> remain.<br><span>Let them fight.</span></div>
      <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:1px;margin:0;">Cross Termination — The Internal War Era — April 22, 2026</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(10)">&#8592; Bylaws</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">12 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn culm" onclick="navTo(12)">⚑ Culmination &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- RANKS & PROMOTIONS -->
  <div id="rankspromo" class="section">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-num">XII</div><div class="sec-line"></div></div>
    <div class="sec-title">Ranks & <span>Promotions</span></div>
    <p>To ascend the ranks within Cross Termination you need to accumulate CTC through active participation and demonstrated proficiency. All promotions must be self-requested through CTBot. Staff will not track your progress automatically.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">How Promotions Work</div>
      <p>Earn CTC through events and operations. Once you meet the requirements for your next rank, run the <strong>apply</strong> command in #bot-stuff. A Pacesetter or Executive will verify your logs and approve. 6 CTC = 1 Robux equivalent.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:40px 0 24px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Pay Structure</div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;">
        <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Company Pay</div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Mercenary Requests</div><div class="record-val">12 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Company Drills</div><div class="record-val">18 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">IW Events / Raids</div><div class="record-val">30 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Official War Events</div><div class="record-val">42 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Exceptional Performance</div><div class="record-val">+12 CTC</div></div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:28px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Leadership Pay</div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Hosting a Company Drill</div><div class="record-val">30 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Hosting an IW Event</div><div class="record-val">42 CTC</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name">Hosting an Official War Event</div><div class="record-val">66 CTC</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:40px 0 24px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Member Rank Requirements</div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Entry</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Cadet</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">Join the CT Roblox Group and verify with Bloxlink</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Read the rules and send acknowledgment reaction</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Training Rank</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Delegator</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">Attend 1 Basic Cadet Training</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Attend 2 events</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 50 CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Company Entry</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Raven / Enforcer</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">Attend and pass Operative Training (Raven OT or Enforcer OT)</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Attend 4 events since becoming Delegator (including OT)</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 90 CTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:40px 0 24px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Inner Company Ranks</div>
      <p style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);letter-spacing:.3px;margin-bottom:16px;">Event count resets at each rank up. Only events after your last promotion count.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;">
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#08121e,var(--black-mid));border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:2px solid var(--raven-dim);padding:24px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--raven);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">Raven Company</div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#7aa8d8;">R1 — Owl</div><div class="record-val">120 CTC · 2 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#7aa8d8;">R2 — Falcon</div><div class="record-val">200 CTC · 3 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#7aa8d8;">R3 — Eagle</div><div class="record-val">300 CTC · 3 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#7aa8d8;">R4 — Vulture</div><div class="record-val">420 CTC · 4 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#7aa8d8;">R5 — Albatross</div><div class="record-val">560 CTC · 4 events</div></div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#120806,var(--black-mid));border:1px solid var(--navy-border);border-top:2px solid var(--enforcer-dim);padding:24px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--enforcer);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">Enforcer Company</div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#d4845a;">R1 — Vanquisher</div><div class="record-val">120 CTC · 2 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#d4845a;">R2 — Phantom</div><div class="record-val">200 CTC · 3 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#d4845a;">R3 — Deathbringer</div><div class="record-val">300 CTC · 3 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#d4845a;">R4 — Conqueror</div><div class="record-val">420 CTC · 4 events</div></div>
          <div class="record-row"><div class="record-name" style="color:#d4845a;">R5 — Dreadbane</div><div class="record-val">560 CTC · 4 events</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:20px 24px;margin-top:2px;">
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:16px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);">Dedicated (2 events/week) — R1 to R5 in ~8 weeks</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);">Casual (1 event/week) — R1 to R5 in ~16 weeks</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:40px 0 24px;">
      <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--navy-border);">Staff Requirements</div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Staff Entry</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Trial Pacesetter</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum R2 in current company</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 4 weeks in faction</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 250 CTC</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Submit the Pacesetter Application</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:8px;letter-spacing:.3px;">Each Pacesetter is required to host a minimum of 2 events per week. Ping FPCS+ to schedule supervised sessions.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">TPCS → FPCS</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Field Pacesetter</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">1 supervised operation + 1 unsupervised operation</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">1 supervised training + 1 unsupervised training</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">110 CTC earned since promotion</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--gold);margin-top:8px;letter-spacing:1px;">= 410+ CTC Total</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">FPCS → DPCS</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Deputy Pacesetter</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">6 operations hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">4 trainings hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">1 game night hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">170 CTC earned since promotion</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--gold);margin-top:8px;letter-spacing:1px;">= 580+ CTC Total</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">DPCS → PCSZ</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Pacesetter Czar</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">10 operations hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">6 trainings hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">2 game nights hosted</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">210 CTC earned since promotion</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:var(--gold);margin-top:8px;letter-spacing:1px;">= 790+ CTC Total</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dd-wrap" style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);margin-bottom:2px;">
        <div class="dd-header" onclick="dd(this)">
          <div><div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:3px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;">Grand Council</div><div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--white);">Executive</div></div>
          <div class="dd-meta"><span class="dd-arrow">▼</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="dd-body">
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 6 weeks in faction</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Minimum 450 CTC</div>
          <div class="bylaw-item">Submit the Executive Application</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:8px;letter-spacing:.3px;">Executive applications are evaluated strictly by the council. Meeting the minimums does not guarantee promotion.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:var(--black-mid);border:1px solid var(--navy-border);padding:20px 24px;margin-top:2px;">
        <div style="font-family:'Rajdhani',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);">TPCS to PCSZ — approximately 2.5 months of consistent hosting activity at minimum quota.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(4)">&#8592; Roles</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">6 / 13</span><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(6)">Events &#8594;</button></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- CULMINATION -->
  <div id="culmination" class="section">
    <div class="culm-lock">
      <div class="culm-lock-border">
        <div class="culm-lock-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="culm-lock-title">ACCESS DENIED</div>
        <div class="culm-lock-sub">Classified — War Council Eyes Only</div>
        <div class="culm-lock-body">This section is restricted to War Council members.</div>
        <div class="error-code">ERROR 403 — CT/WARCOUNCIL/[CULMINATION] — CLEARANCE INSUFFICIENT</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-nav"><div><button class="sec-nav-btn" onclick="navTo(11)">&#8592; Ranks & Promotions</button></div><span class="sec-nav-label">13 / 13</span><div></div></div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
function dd(el){
  var body=el.nextElementSibling;
  var arrow=el.querySelector('.dd-arrow');
  var open=body.classList.contains('open');
  body.classList.toggle('open',!open);
  if(arrow) arrow.classList.toggle('open',!open);
}
function enterSite(){
  var landing=document.getElementById('landing');
  landing.style.transition='opacity .6s ease';
  landing.style.opacity='0';
  setTimeout(function(){landing.style.display='none';},600);
}
const NAV_IDS=['home','mission','history','record','roles','rankspromo','events','systems','defection','diplomacy','bylaws','vote','culmination'];
function navTo(i){
  var id=NAV_IDS[i];
  var btn=document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn')[i];
  show(id,btn);
}
function show(id,btn){
  document.querySelectorAll('.section').forEach(function(s){s.classList.remove('active');});
  document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn').forEach(function(b){b.classList.remove('active');});
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  if(btn) btn.classList.add('active');
  window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'});
}
setTimeout(function(){
  document.querySelectorAll('.vote-bar-fill').forEach(function(b){
    var w=b.style.width;b.style.width='0';
    setTimeout(function(){b.style.width=w;},100);
  });
},300);
</script>
</body>
</html>
